[Matthew 27:50](../../../bib/kjv/mat027.htm#050.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_050">mat 27:50</span></span>

yielded up

Literally, "dismissed his spirit." The (Greek, "aphiēmi"). This
expression, taken with ([Mar 15:37](../../../bib/kjv/mar015.htm#037).md);
([Luk 23:46](../../../bib/kjv/luk023.htm#046).md); ([Joh
19:30](../../../bib/kjv/joh019.htm#030).md). differentiates the death of
Christ from all other physical death. He died by his own volition when
He could say of His redemptive work, "It is finished." "No man taketh it
from me, but I lay it down of myself" ([Joh
10:18](../../../bib/kjv/joh010.htm#018).md).

[Matthew 27:51](../../../bib/kjv/mat027.htm#051.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_051">mat 27:51</span></span>

veil

The veil which was rent was the veil which divided the holy place into
which the priests entered from the holy of holies into which only the
high priest might enter on the day of atonement,

(See Scofield) - ([Exo 26:31](../../../bib/kjv/exo026.htm#031).md); ([Lev
16:1-30](../../../bib/kjv/lev016.htm#001).md).

The rending of that veil, which was a type of the human body of Christ
([Heb 10:20](../../../bib/kjv/heb010.htm#020).md) signified that a "new and
living way" was opened for all believers into the very presence of God
with no other sacrifice or priesthood save Christ's.

Compare ([Heb 9:1-8](../../../bib/kjv/heb009.htm#001).md); ([Heb
10:19-22](../../../bib/kjv/heb010.htm#019).md).

[Matthew 27:52](../../../bib/kjv/mat027.htm#052.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_052">mat 27:52</span></span>

graves

That these bodies returned to their graves is not said and may not be
inferred. The wave-sheaf ([Lev
23:10-12](../../../bib/kjv/lev023.htm#010).md) typifies the resurrection of
Christ, but a sheaf implies plurality. It was a single "corn of wheat"
that fell into the ground in the crucifixion and entombment of Christ
([Joh 12:24](../../../bib/kjv/joh012.htm#024).md); it was a sheaf which
came forth in resurrection. The inference is that these saints, with the
spirits of "just men made perfect" ([Heb
12:23](../../../bib/kjv/heb012.htm#023).md) from Paradise, went with Jesus
([Eph 4:8-10](../../../bib/kjv/eph004.htm#008).md) into heaven.

